research_municipality_step.notes: Jackson Township operates under a mayor-council form of government. There was a discrepancy in sources regarding the current Mayor. Wikipedia states Michael Reina's term ends December 31, 2026, while the Ocean County Government Directory lists Jennifer L. Kuhn as Mayor. Given the specific term end date for Michael Reina, he is listed as Mayor. The Township Council members are based on the Jackson Township Staff Directory and the recent election of Christopher Pollak. Council members are elected at-large, so no divisions are applicable.
